  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "1db86f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 0,
      "content": "IMPORTANT MAJOR INFORMATION",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "11b86f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "Iranian Studies at UCLA encompasses two fields of concentration: Persian and Old Iranian. The Persian track covers the New Persian language, literature, and Islamic philosophy. The Old Iranian track is mainly directed towards students interested in the languages and cultures of the Ancient world, notably, the Ancient Near East (Assyria, Babylonia, and Elam), the Greco-Roman world, as well as Indo European and Indic studies. It deals with the languages, literary traditions, history, and religions of Ancient, pre-Islamic, Iran. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One year of college level coursework in the declared language OR At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was the declared language. Completion of two years of college level foreign language is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For information regarding preparation for this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https://nelc.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation required for this major, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>Iranian Studies at UCLA encompasses two fields of concentration:&nbsp;Persian&nbsp;and&nbsp;Old Iranian. The&nbsp;Persian&nbsp;track covers the New Persian language, literature, and Islamic philosophy. The&nbsp;Old Iranian&nbsp;track is mainly directed towards students interested in the languages and cultures of the Ancient world, notably, the Ancient Near East (Assyria, Babylonia, and Elam), the Greco-Roman world, as well as Indo European and Indic studies. It deals with the languages, literary traditions, history, and religions of Ancient, pre-Islamic, Iran.</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One year of college level coursework in the declared language OR</li><li>At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was the declared language.</li></ul><p>Completion of two years of college level foreign language is <strong>STRONGLY RECOMMENDED</strong>.</p><p>A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses</p><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For information regarding preparation for this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <a href=\"http://www.nelc.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://nelc.ucla.edu</a> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.admission.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">admission.ucla.edu</a>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation required for this major, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "a7bd3237-cc93-4733-9442-019b944ec7d8",
